# Cloudflare Pages cache headers.
#
# Vite emits content-hashed filenames under /assets/ — index-<hash>.js,
# index-<hash>.css, HundredPeople-<hash>.js, the per-region PNG icons,
# etc. The hash changes whenever the source changes, so these URLs are
# safely cacheable for a long time (no stale-content risk: a new build
# produces a new URL the HTML references). Cloudflare Pages defaults to
# a conservative ~10 min TTL; PageSpeed flagged the resulting 60 KiB of
# "use efficient cache lifetimes" savings on repeat visits.
#
# `immutable` is the second half of the win: tells the browser not to
# revalidate at all during the max-age window. Combined with the 1-year
# TTL, repeat visitors get zero network round-trips on every asset.
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
